342
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:25,713
He'll talk if he wants to tell you anything.

343
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,877
We just come in.

344
00:23:32,840 --> 00:23:34,273
Well, next time answer when you're spoke to.

345
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,432
What are you pickin on him for? He ain't done nothin to you.

346
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,238
Are you drawin cards this hand?

347
00:23:44,040 --> 00:23:45,075
I might.

348
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:50,438
Well, I'll see you get a chance to ante.

349
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:02,199
What's he got on his shoulder?  Lennie didn't say nothin to him.

350
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:07,192
Well, I'll tell you what.  Curley's like a lot of little guys- He hates big guys.

351
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,110
It's kinda like he's mad at em cause he ain't a big guy.

352
00:24:10,480 --> 00:24:13,074
You've seen lots o little guys, ain't you?  Always scrappin.

353
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:15,073
Curley sounds like a skunk to me.

354
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:16,953
I hate mean little guys.

355
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:22,394
It seems to me like Curley's the worst.  Got married a couple months ago, his wife lives over in the boss' house.

356
00:24:23,080 --> 00:24:25,514
Seems like Curley's got worse since he got married-

357
00:24:25,514 --> 00:24:27,240
Like he's sitten on an ant hill.

358
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:29,719
Maybe he's showin off for his wife.

359
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:32,756
Yes. You just wait'll you see Curley's wife.

360
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:36,995
One, two. One, two.

361
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,828
The two new buckers showed up, Curley.

362
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:48,836
I've seen 'em, Dad.

363
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:50,515
Don't like their looks much.

364
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,548
Well, I'm not gonna hold that against them.

365
00:24:53,240 --> 00:24:55,629
We wouldn't have a man on the place if I waited for you to like somebody's looks.

366
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,994
If I didn't watch 'em like a hawk every minute, we wouldn't have a place.

367
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,430
Seen Mae?

368
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,234
Oh, let her alone for a minute.

369
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,394
Why do you keep pesterin her?

370
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:06,830
She ain't doin no harm.

371
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,111
How do I know that?

372
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:13,990
Y'know, maybe if Mae had some women to talk to...

373
00:25:14,280 --> 00:25:15,190
It ain't women I'm worried about.

374
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,593
Ah, stick to your job, and forget your wife for an hour.

375
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:43,394
You sure trust me, don't ya, Curley?

376
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:45,673
As far as I can spit.

377
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,000
Who's in there with you?

378
00:25:48,035 --> 00:25:49,513
There ain't nobody in there.

379
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,470
Ya punch drunk pug- I ain't even seen the boy.

380
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,239
He must have just come in.

381
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:22,557
Get out of here!

382
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:25,073
Next time, they'll carry you out.

383
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:30,391
This'll happen to any guy I catch with you.

384
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,555
What did I ever do to give you the right to treat me like..

385
00:26:33,880 --> 00:26:34,596
Nothing.

386
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:36,512
But I ain't takin no chances.

387
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:39,071
You got a home. You got a husband.

388
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,518
You got no business messing around.

389
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:43,313
Sure I got a home.

390
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:46,514
Ya think all I wanna do is sit in that 2x4 just waitin for ya?

391
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:48,828
I want to see somebody.

392
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:51,432
Just see 'em, and talk to 'em.

393
00:26:51,760 --> 00:26:53,512
I tell you, I just want to talk to somebody!

394
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:55,949
You got me to talk to ya.

395
00:26:56,640 --> 00:27:01,360
Yes. I lead with my left twice, see.  Then I bring the ol' right cross.

396
00:27:01,395 --> 00:27:04,177
One, two. One, two and down.

397
00:27:04,212 --> 00:27:06,959
One, two. I can hear it in my sleep.

398
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:13,669
Where did ya get that pup?

399
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:15,075
He was given to me.

400
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:16,350
Slim gave him to you, didn't he?

401
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:17,317
And what if he did?

402
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:18,755
No guy's giving my wife presents.

403
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:21,034
You're giving that pup back.

404
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:22,316
Oh yeah?

405
00:27:23,920 --> 00:27:25,880
If you're not giving it back, Slim's gonna take it back.

406
00:27:25,915 --> 00:27:27,677
No- He's not afraid of you.

407
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,194
We'll see whether he is or not.

408
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,718
Wait'll he takes the ol' "one-two".

409
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:35,996
One, two.

410
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:40,308
One, two.

411
00:27:59,360 --> 00:28:02,040
Hey, Slim!

