00:34:08,240 --> 00:34:08,990
Sure I will.

514
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:10,669
I won't say a word.

515
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:12,513
Do not let them pull you in.

516
00:34:13,720 --> 00:34:16,075
But if he takes a sock at ya, let him have it.

517
00:34:18,560 --> 00:34:19,549
Let him have what, George?

518
00:34:21,280 --> 00:34:21,951
Never mind.

519
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:28,392
Look- if you get into any kind of trouble, do you remember what I told you?

520
00:34:30,200 --> 00:34:33,078
That if I get in any trouble ...

521
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:36,191
you ain't gonna let me tend the rabbits.

522
00:34:36,600 --> 00:34:37,715
That ain't what I mean...

523
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:40,357
Do you remember where we slept last night?

524
00:34:42,680 --> 00:34:43,635
Down by the river?

525
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:46,193
Oh, sure- I remember that.

526
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:51,515
I go there and hide in the brush until you come.

527
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:52,165
That's it.

528
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:54,634
You hide until I come for ya. Now say that over.

529
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:58,034
Hide in the brush by the river.

530
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:01,108
Down in the brush by the river.

531
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:03,034
If you get into trouble.

532
00:35:03,400 --> 00:35:04,960
If I get into trouble.

533
00:35:04,995 --> 00:35:05,631
That's it.

534
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:08,549
Hide in the brush by the river.

535
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:11,710
Down in the brush by the river.

536
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:14,996
Hide in the brush by the river.

537
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:44,949
I'll take them, Slim-

538
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:48,550
I was just given the pups some milk, Slim.

539
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:50,469
She's feelin fine.

540
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:51,631
Thanks, Candy.

541
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,871
Curley ain't been messin around with the pups, has he?

542
00:35:57,200 --> 00:35:58,110
I ain't seen him, Slim.

543
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:01,319
How are ya, Slim-  How'd it go today?

544
00:36:01,354 --> 00:36:03,278
Pretty good, we got two good men now.

545
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:04,916
That so? 

546
00:36:04,916 --> 00:36:07,360
Glad to know ya.  My name's Carlson.

547
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:08,475
My name's George Milton.

548
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:10,992
This here's my partner, Lennie Small.

549
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:15,552
He ain't very small.  No, he ain't small at all.

550
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:20,275
Here ya are, Lennie ... A brown and white one.

551
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:39,394
How many pups ya got left, Slim?

552
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:40,835
I gave this to Curley's wife.

553
00:36:41,720 --> 00:36:42,470
Got two left.

554
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:43,640
Are you gonna keep em both?

555
00:36:43,675 --> 00:36:44,197
I dont know.

556
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:46,951
Got to keep em a while to drink up Lula's milk.

557
00:36:48,560 --> 00:36:53,111
You know, Slim? That ol dog of Candy's, he's so old he can hardly walk.

558
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:58,030
Every time Candy brings him in the bunkhouse, I can smell him for two or three days.

559
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:00,400
Why don't ya get Candy to shoot the old dog, 

560
00:37:00,435 --> 00:37:02,391
and give him one of them pups to raise up.

561
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:12,797
Cmon, Let's wash up. There'll be nothin left to eat in a few minutes.

562
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:19,634
Kind of put you on the spot-

563
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:23,032
Lennie- put that pup back a while. Come and wash up.

564
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:25,278
I'm coming, George.

565
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:28,672
Very been very nice of you to give Lennie that pup.

566
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:31,111
Ah, it wasn't nothing.  No need to thank me for that.

567
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:34,910
Well, it wasn't much to you, maybe, but it's a lot to him.

568
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:37,430
I do not know how we're gonna get him to sleep in the bunkhouse tonight-

569
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:39,353
He'll want to stay right out here in the barn.

570
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:43,078
Gonna have trouble keepin him from gettin right in that box with those pups.

571
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:44,957
What do we do? Catch a shower?

572
00:37:44,992 --> 00:37:46,154
You can catch a shower any time.

573
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:48,672
The only dish out that grub once.

574
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:49,791
Lennie!

575
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:52,309
You sure were right about him-

576
00:37:53,160 --> 00:37:54,513
I never seen such a worker.

577
00:37:55,160 --> 00:37:56,957
I thought he was gonna kill you buckin that barley.

578
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,910
You just tell Lennie what to do and he'll do it.

579
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:01,509
If it don't take no figurin'.

580
00:38:02,840 --> 00:38:04,319
Funny, you and him stringin along together.

581
00:38:04,960 --> 00:38:05,915
What's so funny about it?

582
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:07,036
I dont know.

583
00:38:07,640 --> 00:38:08,629
Just seems kind of funny-

584
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:11,312
cuckoo like him and a smart guy like you.

585
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:14,678
He ain't no cuckoo- He's dumb, but he ain't crazy.

586
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:20,473
And I ain't so smart, neither- 
I wouldn't be buckin barley for my 50 and fun.

587
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:26,389
If I was bright; if I was even a bit smarter,

588
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:28,989
I'd have a place of my own.  Bringin in my own crops.

589
00:38:29,920 --> 00:38:33,435
Instead of doing all the work and not gettin what comes up outta the ground.

590
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:35,394
Yeah, I'd kinda like to do that.

591
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:39,432
I sometimes'd like to cuss out a string of mules that was my own mules

592
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:40,511
Sure-

593
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:44,830
It ain't so funny about me and Lennie travelin together-

594
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:46,710
We growed up together.

595
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:49,112
At first, I made fun of Lennie-

596
00:38:51,520 --> 00:38:54,398
I used to play jokes on him, cause he was too dumb to take care of himself.

597
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:58,759
He was too dumb to know that jokes was bein played on him.

598
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:01,790
Yes. I had fun.

599
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:05,436
It made me seem smart, alongside of him.

600
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,753
Yeah, I seen it that way.

601
00:39:08,160 --> 00:39:10,037
I'll tell you what made me stop playin jokes.

602
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:13,878
There was a bunch of us standing along side the Sacramento River.

603
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:18,077
I was feelin kind of show-off, see, so I turns to Lennie and I says

604
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:21,078
"Jump in".    - What happened?

605
00:39:21,078 --> 00:39:22,200
He jumps

606
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:25,509
He couldn't swim a stroke, so he nearly drowned.

607
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:29,592
And he was so nice to me, because I pulled him out.

608
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:31,996
See, he clean forgot I told him to jump in.

609
00:39:32,960 --> 00:39:34,473
I never done anything like that since.

610
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:38,031
It makes me feel kinda sick talkin about it.

611
00:39:39,600 --> 00:39:40,157
Lennie!

612
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:43,312
I'll go wash up pretty soon, George.

613
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:44,470
You go now-

614
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,990
I'll tell Slim not to let you have that pup.

615
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:48,753
I'm goin...

616
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:52,989
Just like a kid, ain't he?

617
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,038
There's no more harm in him than a kid, neither.

618
00:39:56,120 --> 00:39:57,075
Except he's so strong.

619
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:13,115
He ain't got enough sense to take care of himself.

620
00:40:13,840 --> 00:40:15,273
That's alright- Nice fella.

621
00:40:16,680 --> 00:40:18,398
A guy don't need no sense to be a nice fella.

622
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,672
Lennie is a nuisance most of the time, 

623
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:26,229
But you get used to goin around with the guy, and ya can't get rid of him.

624
00:40:26,560 --> 00:40:27,436
Do you want to get rid of him?

625
00:40:29,320 --> 00:40:30,878
He gets in trouble all the time.

626
00:40:31,960 --> 00:40:33,029
Like he done in Weed.

627
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:36,230
You wouldn't tell anybody, would ya?

628
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:37,271
What did he do in Weed?

629
00:40:37,760 --> 00:40:38,875
You wouldn't tell anybody, would ya?

630
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:42,195
No, of course you wouldn't-

631
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:43,430
What did he do in Weed?

632
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:48,836
Well, there was this girl come along in a red dress-

633
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:52,029
Here he comes. I'll tell you later.

634
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:55,198
I done just like you told me, George.

635
00:40:55,640 --> 00:40:55,958
That's fine.

636
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:58,389
Eat your supper.

637
00:40:59,140 --> 00:41:01,220
It's brown and white, just like I wanted.

638
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:03,772
Ain't you gonna take me to the movies, like ya promised?

639
00:43:04,480 --> 00:43:06,198
I seen it the other night with some of the boys.

640
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,076
Hello Slim-

641
00:44:25,920 --> 00:44:26,875
Hello George.

642
00:44:28,160 --> 00:44:29,354
Don't neither of you play any horshoes?

643
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:30,949
I don't like to play every night.

644
00:44:33,320 --> 00:44:36,500
You guys got a slug of whiskey? I gotta cramp.

645
00:44:36,500 --> 00:44:37,500
I ain't.

646
00:44:37,500 --> 00:44:39,280
If I had any, I'd drink it myself.

647
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:41,395
I ain't got no cramp, neither.

648
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:45,500
Cabbage does it to me- Know'd it was gonna, afor I et it.

649
00:45:06,560 --> 00:45:09,393
You ought've seen that stable buck Bitshune-

650
00:45:10,320 --> 00:45:12,197
He never give nobody a chance to win.

651
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:15,759
Man alive, that dog smells.

652
00:45:16,360 --> 00:45:17,315
Candy, get him out of here.

653
00:45:18,120 --> 00:45:20,429
I don't know nothin smells as bad as old dog smell

654
00:45:21,320 --> 00:45:22,548
I been around him so much, 

655
00:45:23,680 --> 00:45:25,033
I've never noticed how he smells.

656
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:26,958
Well, I can't stand him in here.

657
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:29,476
That smell hangs around even after he's gone.

658
00:45:33,080 --> 00:45:36,000
Look at him, Candy- The old fella's all stiff with rheumatism. 

659
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,320
He ain't no good to ya.

660
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:39,309
Why don't you shoot him?

661
00:45:42,560 --> 00:45:46,300
I tell ya what, Mr. Carlson,  I had him so long.

662
00:45:46,400 --> 00:45:47,500
I herded sheep with him-

663
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:49,836
You wouldn't think to look at him now, 

664
00:45:49,836 --> 00:45:53,040
But he was the best sheep dog I ever seen

665
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:56,500
I knowd a guy in Weed with an Airdale that could herd sheep. 

666
00:45:56,500 --> 00:45:58,520
Learned it from the other dogs.

667
00:45:59,520 --> 00:46:02,432
That old fella just suffers hisself all the time-

668
00:46:03,560 --> 00:46:05,437
If you was to take him out and shoot him, 

669
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:07,514
Right in the back of the head.

670
00:46:10,680 --> 00:46:11,590
Why, he'd never know what hit him.

671
00:46:24,240 --> 00:46:25,229
So you won't shoot him.

672
00:46:25,800 --> 00:46:28,268
No. I couldn't do that.  

673
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:31,077
I had him too long.

674
00:46:31,440 --> 00:46:32,953
He don't have no fun no more-

675
00:46:33,720 --> 00:46:34,869
Besides he smells bad.

676
00:46:36,920 --> 00:46:37,796
I tell you what I'll do.

677
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:41,510
I'll shoot him for ya, so it won't be you that done it.

678
00:46:42,040 --> 00:46:46,350
Leave him alone, Carl. It ain't a guys dog that matters,

679
00:46:46,360 --> 00:46:48,112
its the way a guy feels about his dog.

680
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:52,750
Me- I wouldn't trade my mutt here for one of them field trial pointers.

681
00:46:53,320 --> 00:46:55,595
Candy ain't bein nice to him, leavin him alive.

682
00:46:57,400 --> 00:46:59,834
LIsten- Slim's hound has that litter now-

683
00:47:00,400 --> 00:47:02,311
I bet you he'd give you one of them pups to raise up.

684
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:04,789
Wouldn't ya, Slim?

685
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:09,994
Yeah, you can have a pup.

686
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:13,988
Carl is right, Candy.

687
00:47:15,760 --> 00:47:17,990
That poor dog ain't no good for himself.

688
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:20,795
I wish someone'd shoot me if I get old and a cripple.

689
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:25,949
Maybe it'd hurt him.  I don't mind takin care of him.

690
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:31,073
He'd be better off dead. The way I'd shoot him, he wouldn't feel nothin.

691
00:47:32,120 --> 00:47:36,040
Say- Have you guys seen this?  Right here- Read that.

692
00:47:36,075 --> 00:47:37,393
I don't want to read nothin.

693
00:47:38,400 --> 00:47:40,197
It'll be over in a minute, Candy- Come on.

694
00:47:41,240 --> 00:47:41,956
Did you see it, Slim?

695
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:43,158
What is this?

696
00:47:43,480 --> 00:47:44,708
Read that- Read it out loud.

697
00:47:45,240 --> 00:47:45,877
- Dear Editor?  - Yeah.

698
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:50,309
I been readin your mag for the past 6 months,

699
00:47:50,960 --> 00:47:52,439
I think its the best on the market.

700
00:47:52,840 --> 00:47:54,398
I like stories by Peter Rand.

701
00:47:55,240 --> 00:47:57,310
I think he is a wingding-

702
00:47:58,000 --> 00:47:59,035
What did you want me to read that for?

703
00:47:59,440 --> 00:48:00,714
Read the name at the bottom.

704
00:48:01,400 --> 00:48:03,152
"Yours for success, William Tanner."

705
00:48:03,680 --> 00:48:04,749
What did you want me to read that for?

706
00:48:05,280 --> 00:48:08,078
You don't remember Bill Tanner; worked here till about three months ago?

707
00:48:08,400 --> 00:48:11,440
Oh- sure- Carl, you remember him, a little guy.

708
00:48:11,475 --> 00:48:12,759
Yeah, Slim.  Yeah, that's the guy.

709
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:21,337
Now, Candy, if you want me to, I'll put the ol fella out of his misery right now.

710
00:48:21,372 --> 00:48:25,675
There's nothing left for him-  Can't eat, can't see- Can't hardly walk.

711
00:48:27,080 --> 00:48:28,125
You aint got no gun-

712
00:48:28,160 --> 00:48:31,200
Yes I have, I have a Luger right here in my bag.

713
00:48:32,234 --> 00:48:33,320
The way I'll shoot him, he won't feel nothin.

714
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:38,199
Maybe tomorrow-  Let's wait till tomorrow.

715
00:48:38,480 --> 00:48:41,077
I don't see no sense in waitin. 

716
00:48:41,077 --> 00:48:44,480
Ya know, I aint got no hankerin for this- I'm a doin it for you.

717
00:48:51,480 --> 00:48:52,629
What do you say, Candy?

718
00:49:06,400 --> 00:49:09,437
Candy, you better let him go.

719
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:20,552
Alright.  You can take him. 

720
00:50:51,960 --> 00:50:56,954
One of my lead mules has a bad hoof-  Gotta get some tar on it.

721
00:51:02,240 --> 00:51:04,356
I bet Lennie's out there in the barn with his pup.

722
00:51:05,800 --> 00:51:09,031
Yeah, bet  he won't ever come back in here, now that he's got a pup.

723
00:51:21,240 --> 00:51:22,878
Anybody like to play a little Rummy?

724
00:51:24,920 --> 00:51:26,194
I'll lay out a few with ya.

725
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:34,872
What's takin him so long?

726
00:51:35,440 --> 00:51:38,432
Lay out some cards, why don't you- we get no Rummy played this way.

727
00:52:27,120 --> 00:52:28,189
I am working!

728
00:53:01,600 --> 00:53:05,388
Hey Slim, I think I better get that other brush.

729
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:14,196
Hey, Lennie- you gotta quit pettin that pup for the night- it aint good for him.

730
00:53:14,480 --> 00:53:16,516
Put him back with his mother and run over to the bunkhouse.

731
00:53:17,520 --> 00:53:22,911
I'll do whatever you say that's good for the pup, you bet- I'm goin right now.

732
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:31,839
Thanks for sendin the big guy out- I gotta talk to you.

733
00:53:32,160 --> 00:53:33,195
You got nothin to say to me.

734
00:53:34,840 --> 00:53:36,512
Please, Slim- I gotta talk to somebody-

735
00:53:37,280 --> 00:53:39,111
or I'll go crazy ...Please-

736
00:53:40,360 --> 00:53:42,237
I ain't meant to live like this.

737
00:53:43,600 --> 00:53:46,194
I'd leave this place, only I've got no money.

738
00:53:47,040 --> 00:53:48,268
My mother won't take me back.

739
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:52,149
I only married Curley to get away from her.

740
00:53:54,280 --> 00:53:58,273
Maybe I ought not say this, but I don't like Curley.

741
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:05,429
No, you oughtn't.  You oughtn't be here. You ought not talk to me or any guy on the ranch.

742
00:54:08,640 --> 00:54:10,517
Go on back to the house where you belong.

743
00:54:13,640 --> 00:54:17,397
I don't want to listen to your troubles. 

744
00:54:17,397 --> 00:54:19,640
You got no troubles except what you bring on yourself.

745
00:54:48,640 --> 00:54:52,349
Poor kid- I should've let her talk.

746
00:55:00,640 --> 00:55:02,240
Any of you guys seen my wife?

747
00:55:02,275 --> 00:55:03,309
She ain't been here.

748
00:55:07,120 --> 00:55:08,030
Where is Slim?

749
00:55:08,320 --> 00:55:11,995
He went out to the barn. Said he had to put some tar on a split hoof.

750
00:55:12,560 --> 00:55:13,685
How long ago did he go?

751
00:55:13,720 --> 00:55:15,631
Oh- 5-10 minutes? I don't know.

752
00:55:20,440 --> 00:55:22,192
I think I might like to see this.

753
00:55:22,480 --> 00:55:23,595
Let's all take a look.

754
00:55:26,640 --> 00:55:29,473
Curley must be spoilin-  He wouldn't start for Slim.

755
00:55:30,640 --> 00:55:32,790
Curley thinks Slim's with his wife, don't he?

756
00:55:33,240 --> 00:55:35,834
Yeah, it looks like it.  Course Slim ain't.

757
00:55:39,880 --> 00:55:43,759
At least I don't think Slim is...  Come on!

758
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:47,032
Did you see Slim out there in the barn?

