990
01:11:21,480 --> 01:11:25,871
Imagine going out and not coming back. What would you do then?

991
01:11:26,440 --> 01:11:28,085
What? What?

992
01:11:28,120 --> 01:11:31,715
Suppose George went to town tonight and you never heard of him no more.  Just suppose that.

993
01:11:32,200 --> 01:11:35,829
He won't do that!  George won't go leave me!  He'll come back!

994
01:11:38,600 --> 01:11:40,955
Don't you think he will?

995
01:11:43,240 --> 01:11:47,800
Do you want me to tell what'd happen?  They'd take you to a booby-hatch.

996
01:11:47,835 --> 01:11:54,273
They will tie you up with a collar like a dog.  Then you'd be just like me.  Livin in a kennel.

997
01:12:03,320 --> 01:12:04,600
You hurt George!

998
01:12:04,635 --> 01:12:05,845
I was just supposin- George ain't hurt!

999
01:12:05,880 --> 01:12:09,873
What are you supposin for?  Ain't nobody gonna suppose no hurt to George!

1000
01:12:10,360 --> 01:12:17,152
Of course they ain't.  But maybe you can see now.  You got George.

1001
01:12:17,880 --> 01:12:21,839
You know he's comin back.  Suppose you didn't have nobody.

1002
01:12:22,560 --> 01:12:25,950
Suppose you can't go to the bunkhouse and play Rummy cause you're black.

1003
01:12:26,720 --> 01:12:28,995
Suppose you have to sit out here and read books.

1004
01:12:29,400 --> 01:12:33,598
Books ain't no good.  A guy needs somebody to talk to him.

1005
01:12:34,240 --> 01:12:37,357
I tell you if you get too lonely, you get sick.

1006
01:12:43,720 --> 01:12:48,874
George won't go away and leave me.  I know George won't do that.

1007
01:12:51,000 --> 01:12:52,789
Lennie...

1008
01:12:52,789 --> 01:12:55,150
Lennie...

1009
01:12:56,160 --> 01:12:59,311
Look, Lennie- I've been figurin out something about the place.

1010
01:13:04,960 --> 01:13:06,279
You can come on in if you want.

1011
01:13:06,840 --> 01:13:09,832
Oh, I don't know.  Course if you want me to-

1012
01:13:10,840 --> 01:13:16,551
Oh, come on in.  Everybody's comin in- You might just as well.  Gettin to be like a racetrack.

1013
01:13:19,960 --> 01:13:24,405
Nice cozy little place you got here.

1014
01:13:24,440 --> 01:13:26,795
Must be nice to have a room all to yourself this way.

1015
01:13:28,200 --> 01:13:32,478
Sure ... and a dung heap under my window.   All to myself.

1016
01:13:32,960 --> 01:13:35,918
About the place-  You said about the place.

1017
01:13:36,600 --> 01:13:42,800
I got it all figured out.  We can make some real money on them rabbits, if we go about it right.

1018
01:13:42,835 --> 01:13:45,553
But I get to tend them-  George says I get to tend them.

1019
01:13:45,840 --> 01:13:47,751
You guys just kiddin yourselves.

1020
01:13:48,320 --> 01:13:50,993
You'll be a swamper here till they take you out in a box.

1021
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:55,314
I seen hundreds of guys come by on the road, knowin ranches.  

1022
01:13:55,760 --> 01:13:59,070
Figures on the back and same fool thing in their head.

1023
01:13:59,440 --> 01:14:04,150
Everyone's got a little piece of land in his head, and never a one of them gets it.

1024
01:14:04,440 --> 01:14:05,645
We are, too.

1025
01:14:05,680 --> 01:14:11,437
It's just like heaven.  Nobody ever gets to heaven.  And nobody gets no land.

1026
01:14:12,080 --> 01:14:16,392
Well, we're gonna do it.  George says we are.  He's got the money right now.

1027
01:14:17,640 --> 01:14:18,765
He's got the money?

1028
01:14:18,800 --> 01:14:23,999
Well, he's got most of it- There's just a little bit more to get.  And George's got the land picked out, too.

1029
01:14:24,920 --> 01:14:28,276
Now, you take 12 rabbits.

1030
01:14:28,680 --> 01:14:35,589
I never seen a guy really do it.  I've seen guys most crazy with loneliness for land-

1031
01:14:35,600 --> 01:14:38,630
But every time a dame or a blackjack game took it away from him.

1032
01:14:38,920 --> 01:14:40,612
Well, they ain't gonna get it this time.

1033
01:14:42,480 --> 01:14:45,472
Let's go to Chuck's Roadhouse.  I got twenty bucks left.

1034
01:14:46,360 --> 01:14:49,989
Whatever I got, that goes for me, too.  Monday starts another month- Yippee!

1035
01:14:53,400 --> 01:14:57,992
Twelve rabbits

1036
01:14:57,992 --> 01:15:02,360
At six months

1037
01:15:03,360 --> 01:15:06,670
If you guys would want a hand to work for nothing, 

1038
01:15:07,280 --> 01:15:12,957
just for his keep, I'd come and lend a hand.  I ain't so crippled I can't work like a mischief.

1039
01:15:13,800 --> 01:15:17,000
Well, alright, but we gotta talk to George about that.

1040
01:15:17,000 --> 01:15:20,200
Now- You take 12 rabbits.

1041
01:15:20,200 --> 01:15:21,189
12 rabbits ...

1042
01:15:21,640 --> 01:15:23,073
Different color rabbits

1043
01:15:23,440 --> 01:15:28,000
Sure, sure.  Twelve rabbits and six months time...

1044
01:15:30,000 --> 01:15:31,800
Uh- got that right here.

1045
01:15:38,200 --> 01:15:41,272
For a second there, George, I thought that little place you told me about was a goner.

1046
01:15:41,760 --> 01:15:44,593
It's off-  Ain't nothin gonna stop us now.

1047
01:15:47,000 --> 01:15:51,000
There's a meetin here tonight-  There's a meetin here tonight..

1048
01:15:51,000 --> 01:15:57,000
I know you by your daily walk- There's a meetin here tonight. (Repeats)

1049
01:16:15,500 --> 01:16:19,360
I told em that they ought not be here, but they come in anyhow.

1050
01:16:20,360 --> 01:16:23,079
Couldn't go to bed like I told you, could you Lennie.

1051
01:16:23,640 --> 01:16:26,154
No- You have to get out in society and flap your big mouth.

1052
01:16:26,840 --> 01:16:29,593
I never done nothin bad, George, honest.

1053
01:16:29,920 --> 01:16:33,117
Look, George. I've been figurin and figurin

1054
01:16:33,480 --> 01:16:36,074
I've even got it doped out how we can make some money on them rabbits.

1055
01:16:38,360 --> 01:16:39,873
I thought you wasn't gonna tell nobody.

1056
01:16:40,800 --> 01:16:43,000
I didn't tell nobody but Crooks.

1057
01:16:43,035 --> 01:16:44,353
What'd you tell him for?

1058
01:16:45,080 --> 01:16:47,960
Look, George, Crooks says that if we let him come in with us...

1059
01:16:47,995 --> 01:16:49,365
Get outta here, both of you.

1060
01:16:49,400 --> 01:16:50,765
But George, Crooks said he'll work...

1061
01:16:50,800 --> 01:16:53,598
Maybe you better go- I ain't sure I want in no more.

1062
01:16:58,040 --> 01:16:59,758
Listen, Crooks. It ain't nothin against you.

1063
01:17:00,280 --> 01:17:02,840
It's just that we said that we wouldn't tell nobody else.

1064
01:17:03,200 --> 01:17:07,751
I know. Them guys comin in here, set and made me forget.

1065
01:17:16,680 --> 01:17:19,956
I suppose you're lookin for Curley.  Well Curley ain't here.

1066
01:17:20,360 --> 01:17:26,435
I know Curley ain't here.  It's Saturday night, isn't it?  Got his arm in a sling, and he went anyhow.

1067
01:17:28,080 --> 01:17:30,080
I come to ask Crooks something.

1068
01:17:30,115 --> 01:17:31,911
You don't want to ask me nothing.

1069
01:17:32,640 --> 01:17:35,950
Saturday night! Everybody's out doin something.

1070
01:17:36,480 --> 01:17:40,758
What am I doin?  Standin here, talkin to a bunch of bindlestiffs.

1071
01:17:41,160 --> 01:17:44,277
You ain't wanted here.  We told ya

1072
01:17:45,000 --> 01:17:47,878
You ain't got sense enough in that chicken head to see that we ain't stiffs.

1073
01:17:48,520 --> 01:17:54,470
You do not know that we got our own ranch to go to.  And our own house.  We ain't gotta stay here.

1074
01:17:54,760 --> 01:18:01,677
We gotta house, we got chickens, we got fruit trees, and we got a place that's 100 times bettern this. And we got friends.

1075
01:18:02,160 --> 01:18:04,196
That's what we got. We got friends.

1076
01:18:04,560 --> 01:18:05,993
You old goat.

1077
01:18:06,800 --> 01:18:10,952
If you had two bits, you'd be in town gettin a drink and suckin the bottom of the glass.

1078
01:18:11,880 --> 01:18:13,074
I know you guys.

1079
01:18:13,480 --> 01:18:16,438
Maybe she'll ask Crooks what she come to ask, and then get home.

1080
01:18:20,680 --> 01:18:22,352
What happened to Curley's hand?

1081
01:18:23,760 --> 01:18:27,753
So it wasn't a machine.  Curley didn't act like he was tellin the truth.

1082
01:18:28,320 --> 01:18:29,680
Cmon Crooks, what happened?

1083
01:18:29,715 --> 01:18:31,005
I wasn't there.  Didn't see it.

1084
01:18:31,040 --> 01:18:36,560
What happened? I won't let on to Curley.  He said he caught it in a gear.  Who done it?

1085
01:18:36,595 --> 01:18:37,913
Nobody done it.

1086
01:18:38,440 --> 01:18:42,360
So you done it.  Well, he had it comin.

1087
01:18:42,395 --> 01:18:43,952
I didn't have no fuss with Curley.

1088
01:18:44,400 --> 01:18:50,350
Maybe now you ain't scared of him no more.  Maybe you'll talk to me sometimes.  Everybody was scared of him.

1089
01:18:51,040 --> 01:18:54,000
Say- I didn't sock Curley.  If Curley had any trouble, its none of our affair.

1090
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:55,000
Ask Curley about it.

1091
01:18:57,000 --> 01:19:02,873
Look- I'm gonna try to tell you somethin.  I tried to tell you to get out-  That didn't do no good.

1092
01:19:02,873 --> 01:19:04,240
So I'm gonna try to tell you in another way-

1093
01:19:04,240 --> 01:19:09,075
Now you see- Us guys got somethin that we're gonna do.

1094
01:19:09,075 --> 01:19:10,680
But if you stick around, you're gonna gum up the works.

1095
01:19:10,680 --> 01:19:14,000
It ain't your fault, but

1096
01:19:14,000 --> 01:19:20,200
Look- If a fella steps on a round pebble, and falls down and breaks his neck, it ain't the pebble's fault.

1097
01:19:20,200 --> 01:19:22,475
But the guy wouldn't of done it if the pebble hadn't been there.

1098
01:19:23,440 --> 01:19:27,991
What are you talking about pebbles for?  If you didn't sock Curley, who did?

1099
01:19:28,440 --> 01:19:30,670
Nobody socked Curley.  He got his hand caught in a machine.

1100
01:19:32,960 --> 01:19:35,633
Where did you get them bruises on your face?

1101
01:19:36,760 --> 01:19:38,432
He caught his hand in a machine.

1102
01:19:38,760 --> 01:19:49,159
So it was you. Maybe you're dumb like they say ya are, and maybe you're the only guy on the ranch with nerve.

1103
01:19:50,400 --> 01:19:51,549
You're a nice fella.

1104
01:19:51,960 --> 01:19:56,317
Listen!  I've tried to give you a break, but I'm not gonna let you mess up what we're gonna do.

1105
01:19:56,317 --> 01:19:57,040
You let that guy alone, and you get outta here.

1106
01:19:57,040 --> 01:20:01,640
You won't tell me what to do- I got a right to talk to anybody I want!

1107
01:20:01,675 --> 01:20:02,709
MIlton!

1108
01:20:21,520 --> 01:20:26,594
You couldn't hardly wait for your pup to get home from his night's drunk  so's you could snitch on me, could ya?

1109
01:20:27,960 --> 01:20:32,875
But you didn't tell him what I know to tell him.

1110
01:20:35,400 --> 01:20:37,518
Who busted your hand, Curley?

1111
01:20:38,680 --> 01:20:40,335
I told you I caught it in a machine.

1112
01:20:40,370 --> 01:20:41,990
I saw that machine last night.

1113
01:20:42,520 --> 01:20:43,157
I told ya.

1114
01:20:43,440 --> 01:20:45,192
And why didn't you tell your old man, so he could can him?

1115
01:20:46,000 --> 01:20:46,725
Double crossing...

1116
01:20:46,760 --> 01:20:51,515
I'll tell you why. Cause you was scared that if you talked, they'd talk, too.

1117
01:20:52,160 --> 01:21:01,910
You were scared to get the horse laugh- Like I'm givin you now.  There's a pug with a crippled hand.

1118
01:21:04,800 --> 01:21:06,074
I ain't even gonna slug ya.

1119
01:21:08,160 --> 01:21:12,039
I'm goin upstairs and pack your junk.  You're gettin outa here.  You and me are through.

1120
01:21:14,040 --> 01:21:18,352
One, two!  The ol' one, two.

1121
01:21:38,940 --> 01:21:39,790
Toothpick?

1122
01:21:39,860 --> 01:21:41,680
That sure was a good breakfast, George.

1123
01:21:42,240 --> 01:21:44,117
Probably the last one we'll get in this place.

1124
01:21:44,400 --> 01:21:48,916
George - Slim says not to worry.  He's went to talk to the boss.

1125
01:21:49,520 --> 01:21:51,190
If you'd only stayed in your place like I told you.

1126
01:21:52,160 --> 01:21:55,789
George- DId you send off the money when you was in town last night?

1127
01:21:56,480 --> 01:21:59,615
How many times do I have to tell you? You guys drive me crazy.

1128
01:21:59,650 --> 01:22:02,750
Don't get sore, George.  I only asked ya...  George-

1129
01:22:03,160 --> 01:22:03,876
What?

1130
01:22:05,280 --> 01:22:06,793
Did you have fun in town?

1131
01:22:07,790 --> 01:22:09,530
We just sat around.

1132
01:22:10,420 --> 01:22:15,290
Susie was crackin jokes.  Guys was just startin out to raise a little puny cain.

1133
01:22:16,440 --> 01:22:18,620
I never been like this in my life.

1134
01:22:18,820 --> 01:22:23,370
You know, just pushing out a dime and a nickel to buy a drink-

1135
01:22:24,365 --> 01:22:27,276
and I think what a lot of carrot seed you can get for 15 cents.

1136
01:22:28,400 --> 01:22:32,440
Not to belittle you and all, but bulk seed, you sure can.

1137
01:22:32,475 --> 01:22:35,113
Seeds-  I can't think of nothin else.

1138
01:22:36,520 --> 01:22:41,435
Well, a guy's gotta have some fun.  I went to a dance hall in Bakersfield once.

1139
01:22:42,440 --> 01:22:48,879
What a place!  Went upstairs on a red carpet-  There's big pictures on the wall.

1140
01:22:49,160 --> 01:22:55,156
So I went and sat in a big soft chair.  There was cigarettes on the table, and they was free.

1141
01:22:56,040 --> 01:22:59,874
Pretty soon a chap comes in with drinks on a tray, and them drinks was free.

1142
01:23:00,320 --> 01:23:05,189
You could take all you want.  Pretty soon a girl comes in.  Said she was hostess.

1143
01:23:05,840 --> 01:23:14,350
She was so polite and nice, quiet and pretty, it made me scared to ask her for a dance.  That was a long time ago.

1144
01:23:15,560 --> 01:23:17,198
Are you sayin all this was free?

1145
01:23:18,040 --> 01:23:19,632
Right up till I was leavin.

1146
01:23:21,160 --> 01:23:23,628
And then how much did them soft chairs set you back?

1147
01:23:24,280 --> 01:23:25,759
15 bucks.

1148
01:23:26,320 --> 01:23:32,031
You had a cigarette and a drink and a look at a pretty dress, and that cost you 15 bucks?

1149
01:23:32,480 --> 01:23:35,517
You just shot a week's pay to walk on the red carpet.

1150
01:23:35,840 --> 01:23:40,834
A week's pay?  Sure.  But I worked weeks all my life.

1151
01:23:41,840 --> 01:23:49,394
I don't remember none of them weeks- but this, nearly 20 years ago, I remember that.

1152
01:23:50,360 --> 01:23:57,630
The girl I met was named Arline, with had a pink silk dress.

1153
01:23:59,960 --> 01:24:03,669
Well, its OK.  You guys ain't gonna get canned.

1154
01:24:04,040 --> 01:24:05,485
You sure, Slim?

1155
01:24:05,520 --> 01:24:08,114
Lucky for you, the boss has to move that grain.

1156
01:24:09,820 --> 01:24:11,630
I bet Curley's wife catches it, though.

1157
01:24:23,280 --> 01:24:30,231
I went clear out the gate, then I remembered your foolish little face.  You're comin with me.

1158
01:24:49,120 --> 01:24:50,678
Whatcha coverin up there?

1159
01:24:52,720 --> 01:24:57,157
Just my pup.  Just my little ol pup.

1160
01:24:59,120 --> 01:25:00,394
He's dead.

1161
01:25:01,040 --> 01:25:08,100
He was so little- I was just playin with him and he made like he was gonna bite me

1162
01:25:08,640 --> 01:25:13,000
And then I made like I was gonna smack him, and

1163
01:25:16,800 --> 01:25:18,120
and then he was dead.

1164
01:25:18,120 --> 01:25:21,100
But don't worry none- He was just a mutt.

1165
01:25:21,100 --> 01:25:24,760
You'll get another one easy- The whole country's full of mutts.

1166
01:25:24,760 --> 01:25:30,000
Yeah- It ain't that so much.  George said if I done any more bad things

1167
01:25:34,480 --> 01:25:36,550
Wait a minute, where are you going?

1168
01:25:37,120 --> 01:25:41,671
I ain't gonna have nothin to do with you.  George said I ain't to talk to you nor nothin.

1169
01:25:42,840 --> 01:25:45,354
Listen- Don't worry about talkin to me.

1170
01:25:46,400 --> 01:25:49,312
You know those guys yellin out there?  They got a tournament.

1171
01:25:49,680 --> 01:25:52,990
None of em aint gonna leave till its over, and it aint gonna be over till dark.

1172
01:25:54,290 --> 01:26:00,340
I ain't supposed to.  George sees me talkin to you, he's gonna be mad.  He told me so.

1173
01:26:00,640 --> 01:26:03,518
What's the matter with me?  I ain't got the right to talk to nobody?

1174
01:26:05,280 --> 01:26:07,605
George says you're gonna get us in a mess.

1175
01:26:07,640 --> 01:26:13,158
What harm am I doin to you?  Seems like they ain't none of them cares how I gotta live.

1176
01:26:20,920 --> 01:26:23,309
Confidentially, I'm goin away from here.

1177
01:26:24,000 --> 01:26:28,437
I gotta make somethin outta myself yet.  I ain't used to livin like this.

1178
01:26:29,760 --> 01:26:32,672
I come from Salinas.  Come there when I was a kid.

1179
01:26:33,880 --> 01:26:36,599
 There was a show comin through there once, and I met one of the actors.

1180
01:26:37,000 --> 01:26:40,037
We're gonna have a little place, and rabbits.

1181
01:26:40,780 --> 01:26:43,510
He said he was going to put me in a movie - Says I was a natural.

1182
01:26:44,111 --> 01:26:48,641
Soon's he got back to Hollywood, he was gonna write me about it-  You listenin?

1183
01:26:50,180 --> 01:26:54,320
I never got that letter.  I always thought my old lady stole it.

1184
01:26:55,420 --> 01:26:57,940
I wasn't gonna stay in a place where you couldn't get nowhere.

1185
01:26:58,120 --> 01:27:01,182
or make somethin outta yourself, or they stole your letters.

1186
01:27:02,940 --> 01:27:05,170
I asked her if she stole them, too, and she said "no".

1187
01:27:06,220 --> 01:27:11,830
so I married Curley and went to the Riverside Dance Palace that same night.

1188
01:27:12,480 --> 01:27:15,597
I sure hope George ain't gonna be mad about that there pup.

1189
01:27:16,040 --> 01:27:23,310
I do not like Curley- I'll leave him.  I'm gonna thumb a ride to Hollywood.

1190
01:27:25,000 --> 01:27:29,278
We goin away from here pretty soon.  This ain't no nice place.

1191
01:27:29,760 --> 01:27:33,429
I'm gonna get in the movies, and wear all them nice clothes.

1192
01:27:34,330 --> 01:27:35,780
I want nice clothes like they wear.

1193
01:27:36,960 --> 01:27:39,840
And I'll set in them big hotels and they'll take pictures of me.

1194
01:27:39,980 --> 01:27:42,920
When they have them opens, I'll go and talk on the radio.

1195
01:27:43,240 --> 01:27:45,440
and it won't cost me nothin because I'm in the picture.

1196
01:27:46,750 --> 01:27:50,720
I want nice clothes like they wear.  This guy says I'm a natural.

1197
01:27:52,280 --> 01:27:56,558
We goin away.  Far away from here.

1198
01:27:57,840 --> 01:28:02,311
Course, when my ol lady hears I run away from Curley, she won't ever speak to me no more.

1199
01:28:03,400 --> 01:28:08,394
She'll think that I aint decent, that's what she'll think.  Well, we ain't really decent-

1200
01:28:08,680 --> 01:28:14,118
no matter what my ol lady tries to hide.  My ol man was a drunk- They put im away.

1201
01:28:15,000 --> 01:28:19,596
One night when I was just a little kid, him and my ol lady had a terrible fight.

1202
01:28:20,080 --> 01:28:21,672
They was always fightin.

1203
01:28:22,520 --> 01:28:26,718
In the middle of the night he come into my room and he says- "let's you and me run away".

1204
01:28:27,560 --> 01:28:34,272
He says we gonna live together.  We gonna live together cause you're my own little girl.

1205
01:28:35,280 --> 01:28:41,719
Why, you'll bake little cakes for me, and I'll paint pretty pictures all over the wall.

1206
01:28:47,320 --> 01:28:49,550
And in the mornin, they caught us and put him away.

1207
01:28:54,640 --> 01:28:57,473
Uh - I wish I woulda went.

1208
01:29:01,520 --> 01:29:06,435
They locked him up for drunk, and in a little while, he died.

1209
01:29:08,160 --> 01:29:13,120
Maybe if I took that there pup and throwed him away, George wouldn't never know.

1210
01:29:13,155 --> 01:29:15,793
Then maybe I could tend the rabbits without no trouble.

1211
01:29:16,840 --> 01:29:17,989
You're goofy.

1212
01:29:18,760 --> 01:29:21,718
No I ain't.  George says I aint.

1213
01:29:22,040 --> 01:29:26,352
I just like to pet nice things- Smooth things.

1214
01:29:26,800 --> 01:29:29,109
Well, who don't?  Everybody likes that.

1215
01:29:29,760 --> 01:29:32,877
I like the feel of silk and velvet! You like the feel of velvet?

1216
01:29:33,640 --> 01:29:38,620
You bet by golly.  I had some, too.  A lady give it to me.

1217
01:29:39,670 --> 01:29:41,560
Aunt Clara-  She give it right to me.

1218
01:29:42,640 --> 01:29:46,620
About this big a piece.  I wish I had that velvet right now.

1219
01:29:49,240 --> 01:29:54,410
I ain't seen it for a long time.  I musta lost it.

1220
01:29:54,940 --> 01:29:56,790
You're goofy.

1221
01:29:57,520 --> 01:30:00,880
But you're kind of a nice fella.  Just like a big baby.

1222
01:30:02,120 --> 01:30:04,360
A person can kinda see what you mean-

1223
01:30:04,760 --> 01:30:09,420
Sometimes, when I'm doin my hair, I just sit there and stroke it cause its so soft.

1224
01:30:10,520 --> 01:30:14,693
Some people got kinda coarse hair- You take Curley.

1225
01:30:15,193 --> 01:30:19,828
His hair is just like wire-  Mine's soft and fine.

1226
01:30:20,940 --> 01:30:21,940
Here- feel.

1227
01:30:23,620 --> 01:30:24,873
Right here.

1228
01:30:30,000 --> 01:30:31,000
Don't you muss it up.

1229
01:30:33,500 --> 01:30:35,000
You're messing it up - Ow!

1230
01:30:35,000 --> 01:30:36,000
Stop and let go!

1231
01:30:37,000 --> 01:30:41,200
Please- Please don't yell-  George is gonna say I done a bad thing!

1232
01:30:44,960 --> 01:30:48,873
Don't do that! You're gonna get me in trouble just like George says you will!

1233
01:31:51,120 --> 01:31:52,269
Lennie!

1234
01:31:53,760 --> 01:31:54,795
Lennie!

1235
01:32:19,020 --> 01:32:23,500
George is gonna be pretty mad at him taking that pup out.

1236
01:32:26,160 --> 01:32:28,677
Slim says I can have one of you guys

1237
01:32:46,500 --> 01:32:47,320
I'll ask im.

1238
01:32:51,020 --> 01:32:52,000
Oh, Slim-

1239
01:33:00,320 --> 01:33:01,740
It's OK, Candy-

1240
01:33:01,930 --> 01:33:03,580
Your old dog wouldn't mind.

1241
01:33:06,020 --> 01:33:08,040
Lonesome for a guy, without a dog.

1242
01:33:08,580 --> 01:33:09,940
He'll have a lot of fun at our little place.

1243
01:33:10,095 --> 01:33:11,520
Sure he could. 

1244
01:33:11,555 --> 01:33:12,325
You seen Lennie in the barn?

1245
01:33:12,360 --> 01:33:14,365
His pup wasn't there.

1246
01:33:14,400 --> 01:33:17,517
He must be out playin with him some place.  Now don't be mad with him, George.

1247
01:33:18,200 --> 01:33:21,112
I gotta get him or he won't remember to get any supper.

1248
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:30,993
Candy! Did that dog follow you out of the barn?  Come on!

1249
01:33:55,520 --> 01:34:00,150
What done it?  George- What done it?

1250
01:34:05,500 --> 01:34:06,800
I should have know'd it.

1251
01:34:07,500 --> 01:34:10,920
I think way back in my head, I did.

1252
01:34:10,920 --> 01:34:13,150
What are we gonna do, George? What are we going to do now?

1253
01:34:17,200 --> 01:34:18,997
We can't let him get away.

1254
01:34:19,360 --> 01:34:24,460
No- we oughta let him get away.  You don't know about Curley- Curley's gonna wanna get him lynched.  Curley's gonna kill him.

1255
01:34:24,680 --> 01:34:27,558
Yes, that's right-  Curley will, and the other guys

1256
01:34:32,000 --> 01:34:38,792
You and me get that little place, won't we George?  You and me can go there, and live nice.

1257
01:34:39,360 --> 01:34:41,794
Can't we George?  ...  Can't we?

1258
01:34:47,240 --> 01:34:49,959
It's all off, I know...  It's all off.

1259
01:34:54,040 --> 01:34:57,565
He was such a nice fella I didn't think he'd do nothin like this.

1260
01:34:57,620 --> 01:35:01,960
Lennie never done it outa meanness.  All the times he done bad things, he never done one of em mean!

1261
01:35:13,080 --> 01:35:16,040
I ain't gonna let em hurt Lennie.

1262
01:35:17,980 --> 01:35:20,290
Listen- I'm goin over to the bunkhouse.

1263
01:35:21,140 --> 01:35:25,589
Then in a minute you come out and tell the guys about her.  I'll come along and make out like I never seen here.  Will you do that?

1264
01:35:25,720 --> 01:35:26,740
Sure, George.

1265
01:35:26,820 --> 01:35:30,080
Give me a minute, and you come out and yell like you just found her.

1266
01:35:30,160 --> 01:35:31,870
Okay, okay ...

1267
01:35:40,560 --> 01:35:46,795
Ya done it, didn't ya.  I suppose you're gonna act- Everybody knows you'd messed things up.

1268
01:35:47,560 --> 01:35:51,050
You wasn't no good.  And you ain't no good now.

1269
01:35:52,660 --> 01:36:00,340
I could have hoe'd the garden, washed the dishes for them guys. Could'a had pigs, and chickens

1270
01:36:00,940 --> 01:36:04,310
And in the winter ... the little fat stove.

1271
01:36:05,160 --> 01:36:10,250
with the wind, and the rain comin- And us just sittin there.

1272
01:36:18,880 --> 01:36:24,876
Hey! Hey! Hey you guys!

1273
01:36:41,360 --> 01:36:43,000
Someone's murdered Curley's wife.

1274
01:36:43,120 --> 01:36:43,960
What?

1275
01:37:12,360 --> 01:37:15,740
I know who done it.  That big guy done it-  I know he done it.

1276
01:37:15,980 --> 01:37:17,710
Why, everyone else was out there playin horseshoes.

1277
01:37:18,480 --> 01:37:19,560
Hey- My Luger's gone- it ain't in my bag.

1278
01:37:19,880 --> 01:37:20,930
Maybe you lost it.

1279
01:37:21,440 --> 01:37:24,760
No- I seen it there this mornin.  It's been took.
Then he's armed.

1280
01:37:25,440 --> 01:37:29,560
Listen, Mr. Jackson. The poor guy didn't know what he was doin.  Tell them not to shoot him.

1281
01:37:29,660 --> 01:37:35,650
Shoot him? He got Carlson's gun, eh?  Sure, I'm gonna shoot him.  I'm gonna get him myself.

1282
01:37:36,480 --> 01:37:37,660
Here they are, Mr. Jackson.

1283
01:37:44,780 --> 01:37:46,220
I suppose we couldn't let him get away?

1284
01:37:46,460 --> 01:37:47,540
Not a chance.

1285
01:37:48,080 --> 01:37:49,760
Couldn't we bring him in, and then lock him up safe?

1286
01:37:50,680 --> 01:37:56,020
If we could only keep Curley here.  But you heard him- He's still mad about his hand.

1287
01:37:58,020 --> 01:38:02,130
Supposin they catch him.  They'll bring him back, strap him down,

1288
01:38:02,260 --> 01:38:06,240
then lock him up in a cage ... That's ain't no good, George.

1289
01:38:06,460 --> 01:38:08,870
I know it...  I know it.

1290
01:38:10,520 --> 01:38:12,430
Got any idea where he mighta went?

1291
01:38:14,720 --> 01:38:17,470
I think there's only one way to get Lennie outa this.

1292
01:39:34,190 --> 01:39:35,730
You want I should go away?

1293
01:39:38,310 --> 01:39:39,520
I'll be close by.

1294
01:39:50,980 --> 01:39:52,120
Lennie?

1295
01:39:55,240 --> 01:39:58,160
You see, George? I come right back here, just like you told me.

1296
01:39:58,460 --> 01:40:01,650
You wasn't gonna go away and leave me, was you, George?

1297
01:40:03,920 --> 01:40:06,720
I heard them guys walking through the woods ...

1298
01:40:06,860 --> 01:40:09,170
What was them guys doin in the woods, George?

1299
01:40:12,120 --> 01:40:13,210
Huntin ...

1300
01:40:14,340 --> 01:40:17,350
Why don't we go with them?  I like huntin.

1301
01:40:21,240 --> 01:40:24,420
Is it- cause I done a bad thing?

1302
01:40:27,760 --> 01:40:29,079
That don't make no difference.

1303
01:40:29,920 --> 01:40:32,040
Is that why we can't go huntin with them guys.

1304
01:40:32,840 --> 01:40:34,490
That don't make no difference.

1305
01:40:37,600 --> 01:40:43,810
George, ... Ain't you gonna ball me out?

1306
01:40:45,520 --> 01:40:46,630
will you have it?

1307
01:40:47,040 --> 01:40:49,720
Sure- like you always done.

1308
01:40:49,890 --> 01:40:55,790
Like if I didn't have you, I could take my 50 bucks,

1309
01:40:55,980 --> 01:40:59,780
Lennie, you can't never remember nothin that happens

1310
01:41:00,840 --> 01:41:03,998
but you remember every word I say, don't you.

1311
01:41:06,200 --> 01:41:10,159
Ain't you gonna say it?  Go on, George- Say it.

1312
01:41:13,920 --> 01:41:18,460
If I was alone- I could live so easy-

1313
01:41:20,320 --> 01:41:24,180
could get me a job ... never have no mess.

1314
01:41:24,390 --> 01:41:25,920
... And when the end of the month comes

1315
01:41:26,880 --> 01:41:31,476
... and when the end of the month comes, I'd take my 50 bucks

1316
01:41:53,280 --> 01:41:57,680
Go on, George. Tell how its gonna be.

1317
01:42:01,880 --> 01:42:05,660
Lennie- I want for you to sit down there.

1318
01:42:08,340 --> 01:42:10,980
And I want for you to look across that river-

1319
01:42:12,920 --> 01:42:15,510
... cause I'm gonna tell you like you could almost see it.

1320
01:42:21,160 --> 01:42:22,440
Go on, George.

1321
01:42:24,000 --> 01:42:27,280
We're gonna have a little place-
We're gonna have a little place-

1322
01:42:28,480 --> 01:42:31,360
We're gonna have cows, pigs and chickens.

1323
01:42:32,460 --> 01:42:36,120
And down on the flat, we're gonna have a field of alfalfa.

1324
01:42:36,640 --> 01:42:39,410
- For the rabbits ... 
- For the rabbits.

1325
01:42:39,480 --> 01:42:40,880
And I get to tend the rabbits?

1326
01:42:41,720 --> 01:42:43,060
Tend the rabbits.

1327
01:42:44,120 --> 01:42:47,380
And we can live off the fat of the land.

1328
01:42:49,180 --> 01:42:54,552
Just keep lookin across that river, like you can really see it.

1329
01:42:55,510 --> 01:42:56,570
Where?

1330
01:42:57,480 --> 01:43:00,620
Right there ... Can't you almost see it?

1331
01:43:00,920 --> 01:43:02,070
Where, George?

1332
01:43:03,360 --> 01:43:05,740
Keep looking ... just keep looking ...

1333
01:43:06,960 --> 01:43:10,720
I'm lookin' George. I'm looking.

1334
01:43:12,810 --> 01:43:14,070
It's gonna be nice, aint I right?

1335
01:43:15,180 --> 01:43:21,470
There ain't gonna be no trouble.  No fights.  There ain't gonna be nobody mean

1336
01:43:24,680 --> 01:43:30,220
Yeah- I can see it! Right over there-  George, I can see it!

1337
01:45:51,080 --> 01:45:56,070
The End
